  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I expect UX/user interaction to be consistent with standards already established in popular apps with same context.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: There is at the moment two main panes in Status desktop - the chat list pane, and the chat pane. When I start scrolling up or down with mouse on one pane, and then roll the mouse over to other pane, the other pane also scrolls.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nScroll event started on a pane usually do not carry over to other pane\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nScroll event initiated on one carries over to the other pane on roll over to other pane\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status Desktop\r\n- Scroll with mouse up/down on Chat list or chat pane, roll mouse over to other pane\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: StatusIm-180923-025918-089027-nightly.dmg \r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS High Sierra",
